[{'text': 'In a previous video we talked about cues and
cue clustering. In this video we are going', 'start': 0.329, 'duration': 5.01}, {'text': 'to discuss how to turn your assessment data
into nursing diagnoses.', 'start': 5.339, 'duration': 5.851}, {'text': 'Many students try to make nursing diagnoses
the hard way. They make the mistake of jumping', 'start': 11.19, 'duration': 4.79}, {'text': 'to conclusions during the assessment phase.
They try to skip cue clustering and just guess', 'start': 15.98, 'duration': 5.32}, {'text': 'at a nursing diagnosis right away instead
of doing a thorough assessment. Then they end up', 'start': 21.3, 'duration': 6.21}, {'text': 'comparing the defining characteristics that
are listed in their handbook for each diagnosis', 'start': 27.51, 'duration': 4.499}, {'text': 'to their patients assessment data. Could
you imagine going through all of the nursing', 'start': 32.009, 'duration': 5.781}, {'text': 'diagnoses for each patient  Wow! You would
never get your assignment done! Plus, if you', 'start': 37.79, 'duration': 6.53}, {'text': 'do that it is likely that you will miss important
information and important diagnoses. You might', 'start': 44.32, 'duration': 5.55}, {'text': 'also misdiagnose the patient because you will
be tempted to just use the first diagnosis', 'start': 49.87, 'duration': 5.39}, {'text': 'that sort of matches what is going on. Dangerous!', 'start': 55.26, 'duration': 5.27}, {'text': 'During assessment if you think you know what
the diagnosis might be dont jump to conclusions', 'start': 60.53, 'duration': 5.5}, {'text': '- make sure you have asked enough questions
and gathered enough data to support your inference.', 'start': 66.03, 'duration': 5.48}, {'text': 'It is good to note your inference then ask
more questions or collect more data to confirm', 'start': 71.51, 'duration': 5.82}, {'text': 'or exclude your inference.', 'start': 77.33, 'duration': 2.94}, {'text': 'Always assess your patient first. The easy
way to make nursing diagnoses is to assess', 'start': 80.27, 'duration': 6.25}, {'text': 'first, cluster cues, investigate any inferences
then identify one or more nursing diagnoses.', 'start': 86.52, 'duration': 7.0}, {'text': 'During your assessment identify any abnormal
data. The abnormal data that you collect will', 'start': 95.11, 'duration': 5.299}, {'text': 'often become the defining characteristics
in the nursing diagnosis. When you construct', 'start': 100.409, 'duration': 5.181}, {'text': 'a nursing diagnosis you essentially work backwards
from the defining characteristics to the diagnostic', 'start': 105.59, 'duration': 5.8}, {'text': 'label, but we will go over the components
of nursing diagnoses in another video.', 'start': 111.39, 'duration': 7.0}, {'text': 'Once you have identified clusters of cues
that seem to fit together it is time to think', 'start': 119.799, 'duration': 4.211}, {'text': 'critically about what the problem could be.
Match your cue clusters to one or more nursing', 'start': 124.01, 'duration': 4.889}, {'text': 'diagnoses by looking up the ones you think
match the assessment data. Then, pick the', 'start': 128.899, 'duration': 5.241}, {'text': 'best nursing diagnoses for your patient.', 'start': 134.14, 'duration': 3.12}, {'text': 'In the real world it is impossible to find
and treat all nursing diagnoses at once, especially', 'start': 137.26, 'duration': 6.53}, {'text': 'when hospital stays are short. Focus on the
most important areas for your patient when', 'start': 143.79, 'duration': 4.99}, {'text': 'creating your diagnoses.', 'start': 148.78, 'duration': 2.25}, {'text': 'Keep in mind that not all of the conclusions
you draw from your assessment will lead to', 'start': 151.03, 'duration': 4.62}, {'text': 'a nursing diagnosis. If you have identified
information that just does not fit into a', 'start': 155.65, 'duration': 5.47}, {'text': 'nursing diagnosis it is possible that it isnt
meant to. The data could be related to a collaborative', 'start': 161.12, 'duration': 6.5}, {'text': 'problem or medical diagnosis instead.', 'start': 167.62, 'duration': 3.28}, {'text': 'Dont panic, you can still have nursing
interventions without a nursing diagnosis.', 'start': 170.9, 'duration': 5.85}, {'text': 'For example, you will still give your patient
medication for a medical diagnoses that is', 'start': 176.75, 'duration': 5.01}, {'text': 'not the main focus of nursing care.', 'start': 181.76, 'duration': 2.27}, {'text': 'If you arent sure what the differences
are between a medical diagnosis, nursing diagnosis', 'start': 184.03, 'duration': 5.37}, {'text': 'and collaborative problem please watch that
